          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Windowless thin 100 mu-m solid deuterium target",
                "formed on a 5.4 mu-m Ag foil backing that faced the",
                "beam direction. A copper shield cooled to 30 K with",
                "an opening for the scattered particles surrounds the",
                "copper target cell cooled to 4 K to reduce the",
                "radiative heating."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD",
                "CSICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The targetlike reaction products, p,",
                "d, t, were identified [by annular dE-E arrays of 100",
                "mu-m thick segmented silicon detectors Si followed by",
                "12 mm thick CsI(Tl) detectors.The silicon detector",
                "array was composed of eight independent sectors",
                "forming an annulus and providing azimuthal",
                "segmentation. Each sector is segmented into 16 rings",
                "which provide the scattering angle. The CsI(Tl) array",
                "was segmented into 16 sectors where two sectors match",
                "one sector of the silicon detector."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD",
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Heavy projectile-like particles were",
                "detected in an array (S3) of double sided Si strip",
                "detectors"
              ]
            }
